div.p: Each downstream cluster runs a custom controller to handle CRD for JitRequests and JitGroupCache

ol.li: Namespace owners/platform admins define above label and annotations to set the approver group for the namespaces in respective cluster.
Per cluster, the controller will cache the namespace group metadata in a JitGroupCache object
On API start-up all JitGroupCache's are fetched from downstream clusters and cached in memory. (cache is refreshed on new access request if 10 minutes have passed since last cache refresh)
Web layer uses the API to validate namespaces in new access requests, cluster and namespace(s) are validated against cached Jit Groups in API layer.
On new access request, API assigns the group ID as per cache as the approver required, per Namespace.
Access request now requires individual owning group approvals, OR can be approved by Admins/Platform Approvers outright.
On approve, API will create the JitRequest object on the downstream cluster
The selected clusters Jit controller will process the JitRequest and call-back to the API layer via HMAC signed URL on status update (pending/rejected/succeeded).

A valid flow would result in the controller call-back with 'Pending' status, scheduling the JitRequest for the requested start date/time, then creating the desired RoleBinding in desired Namespaces and deleting on End Date/Time.
Email notification sent to requestor on new request, approver/reject, pending, success/completion.
